---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Terms · thelnk" description="Terms of use for thelnk.is.">
  <article class="legal">
    <h1>Terms of use</h1>
    <p class="lead">Last updated: May 2026</p>

    <h2>The service</h2>
    <p>
      thelnk.is provides URL shortening and temporary file sharing. The service is offered as-is. We may change,
      limit, or discontinue features with reasonable notice where practicable.
    </p>

    <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
    <p>
      You may not use the service to distribute malware, conduct phishing, harass others, violate applicable law, or
      infringe intellectual property. We may suspend links or accounts that abuse the service or threaten its
      stability.
    </p>

    <h2>Free and anonymous links</h2>
    <p>
      Links created without signing in are subject to per-link use limits described on the homepage. We do not
      guarantee indefinite availability of any specific link.
    </p>

    <h2>Uploaded files and promotional use</h2>
    <p>
      If you use the service on a <strong>free or anonymous account</strong> (including when you are signed in but do
      not have an active Pro or Lifetime entitlement), you agree that by uploading files you <strong>opt in</strong> to
      thelnk.is using those files for public use, display, or distribution in any manner we reasonably choose in
      connection with operating, improving, or promoting the service (for example marketing materials, demos, social
      posts, or editorial features), without owing you compensation or providing further notice for such uses. You
      represent that you have all rights necessary to grant this permission for content you upload.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Pro and Lifetime subscribers</strong> are entitled to exclude their uploads from discretionary
      promotional use as described above. You may do so by signing in and enabling <strong>account privacy</strong> in
      your account settings. While account privacy is on and your paid entitlement is active, we will not use files you
      upload under that account for discretionary public promotion in the manner described for free users. Core
      operation of the service (for example storing and serving files to people you share links with) is not
      “promotion” for purposes of this section.
    </p>

    <h2>Subscriptions</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>Pro monthly</strong> is billed through Stripe until you cancel in the Stripe customer flow (or your payment method fails and the subscription ends). When the subscription is no longer active, your account returns to the free tier limits described on the homepage.
    </p>

    <h2>Lifetime license</h2>
    <p>
      A one-time purchase grants the account linked at checkout access to paid-tier limits described on the homepage
      (for example unlimited successful uses per link you create while your account remains in good standing). “Lifetime”
      means for the operational lifetime of the service, not a literal eternity. If we wind down the product, we will
      make reasonable efforts to give notice and a data export window where feasible.
    </p>

    <h2>Refunds</h2>
    <p>
      Digital access is delivered immediately after successful payment. Refunds are handled case-by-case; contact
      support within 14 days of purchase if you believe you were charged in error.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes to pricing, features, and limits</h2>
    <p>
      We reserve the right to adjust <strong>pricing</strong>, <strong>features</strong>, and <strong>limits</strong>
      (including upload size caps, per-link use allowances, storage or retention periods, and other quotas) whenever we
      consider it appropriate to operate, improve, or sustain the service. Homepage and marketing descriptions are
      guidance and may be updated. Where a change would materially affect existing paying subscribers, we will make
      reasonable efforts to provide advance notice when practicable, consistent with law and payment-provider rules.
    </p>

    <h2>Disclaimer</h2>
    <p>
      To the maximum extent permitted by law, the service is provided without warranties of any kind. We are not
      liable for indirect or consequential damages arising from use of the service.
    </p>

    <p><a href="/">← Home</a></p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal {
    max-width: 40rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 3rem 1.5rem 4rem;
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--muted);
  }
  .legal h1 {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.25rem);
    color: var(--text);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }
  .legal .lead { margin: 0 0 2rem; color: var(--muted); }
  .legal h2 {
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: var(--text);
    margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem;
  }
  .legal p { margin: 0 0 1rem; }
  .legal a { color: var(--accent); }
</style>
